akn:content.akn:p: § 59p. Kenduskeag Stream, Penobscot County, Maine The Kenduskeag Stream, a minor tributary of the Penobscot River, located in Penobscot County, in the State of Maine, be, and the same is hereby, declared to be a nonnavigable waterway within the meaning of the Constitution and laws of the United States of America. The right of Congress to alter, amend, or repeal this section is hereby expressly reserved. (July 11, 1947, ch. 236, 61 Stat. 316.)
